#markdown-help
  h1 Formatting Help

  b This page uses Markdown formatting. Please refer to the guide below for help.
  hr

  h2 General notes
  p Adjacent lines will be combined into a single paragraph.
  p To start a new paragraph, separate it with a blank line above it.
  p To enter a manual line break within a paragraph, end a line with two spaces.
  hr

  #markdown-details
    h2 Paragraph Formatting
    p These control symbols must be the first character(s) of a paragraph.

    h3 Headings
    p Heading symbols must be separated from their text by a space.
    p Ideally, headings should be arranged hierarchically.
    p.i Do not use more than one Title on any page.
    h1
      span.bold.red> #
      | Title
    h2
      span.bold.red> ##
      | Heading
    h3
      span.bold.red> ###
      | Sub-Heading
    h4
      span.bold.red> ####
      | Section Heading
    h5
      span.bold.red> ######
      | Sub-Section Heading
    h6
      span.bold.red> ######
      | Sub-Sub-Section Heading

    h3 Other Paragraph Styles
    p
      span.bold.red @
      | Center align
    p
      span.bold.red +
      span.bigger.bold Bigger and Bold
    hr

    h2 Inline Text Formatting
    p These control symbols must surround and be in contact with the text to be affected, and must then be separated by blank space on either side.
    p
      span.bold.red
        | *
      span.italic Italic
      span.bold.red
        | *

    p
      span.bold.red
        | **
      b Bold
      span.bold.red
        | **

    p
      span.bold.red
        | ***
      b.italic Bold Italic
      span.bold.red
        | ***

    p
      span.bold.red _
      u Underline
      span.bold.red _

    p
      | Text with
      span.bold.red ^
      sup superscript

    p
      span.bold.red ~~
      strike Strikethrough
      span.bold.red ~~
    hr

    h2 Links
    p Bare URLs (e.g. <b>https://bpsd9.org</b>) will be automatically linked.
    pre
      span.bold.red
        | [
      | Page Name
      span.bold.red
        | ](
      | http://example.com/some/path
      span.bold.red )
    pre
      span.bold.red
        | [
      | Local Page
      span.bold.red
        | ](
      | /some/path
      span.bold.red )

    h3 Email Links
    p You can specify an email address in a link.
    pre
      span.bold.red
        | [
      | Email Name
      span.bold.red
        | ](
      | example@example.com
      span.bold.red )

    h3 Reference Links
    p You can specify reusable links, or simply define the URL for a link somewhere else in the page by using the following syntax:
    pre
      span.bold.red
        | [
      | Link Name
      span.bold.red
        ' ]:
      | http://example.com/some/path
    p To use one of these links in the page, reference it like this:
    pre
      span.bold.red
        | [
      | Link Text to Display
      span.bold.red
        | ] [
      | Link Name
      span.bold.red
        | ]
    hr

    h2 Image
    pre
      span.bold.red ![
      | Image description
      span.bold.red ](
      | http://example.com/some/path/image.png
      span.bold.red )
    hr

    h2 Horizontal line
    pre: span.bold.red ---
    hr

    h2 Bulleted list
    p You must leave a blank line on both sides of a bulleted list.
    p You must leave a space between the dash and text.
    p
      ' You can indent items one level by preceding the
      span.bold.red> -
      | with two spaces
    pre
      span.bold.red> -
      | Item 1
      br
      span.bold.red> -
      | Item 2
    hr

    h2 Table
    p
      ' You can create a table using
      span.bold.red> |
      ' and
      span.bold.red> -
      | as shown below.
    p
      ' You can also add
      span.bold.red
        ' :
      ' at the ends of the row of
      span.bold.red> -
      | to specify the alignment of each column. (The default is left.)
    p
      pre
        span.bold.red |
        | &nbsp;Header&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;Center Header&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Right Header
        span.bold.red  |
        br
        span.bold.red |------------|:---------------:|----------------:|
        br
        span.bold.red |
        | &nbsp;Item 1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Item 2.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Item 3.1
        span.bold.red  |
        br
        span.bold.red |
        | &nbsp;Item 1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
        | &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
        span.bold.red  |
    hr

    h2 Uploaded files
    p
      | To link to uploaded files or display uploaded images, go to the #{link_to('upload files page', file_path)} and copy the "Markdown key"
      br
      | into where you want it to display on the page.
    p The format of these keys follows this pattern:
    pre
      span.bold.red %file/
      | 7
      span.bold.red
        | /
      | Customizable link text
      span.bold.red
        | /
    hr

    h2 FontAwesome Pro Icons
    p The #{link_to("FontAwesome Pro", "https://fontawesome.com/icons?d=listing", target: :_blank)} icon library is available, if you want to use a particular icon somewhere in a page.

    h3 General Usage
    pre
      span.bold.red %fa/
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | /
    pre
      span.bold.red %fa/
      | icon-name
      span.bold.red
        | :
      | css
      span.bold.red
        | /

    h3 Styling
    p You can specify arbitrary CSS classes on each icon. (Separate classes with spaces.)

    h4 Colors
    p
      ul
        li.bold.birmingham-blue birmingham-blue
        li.bold.blue blue
        li.bold.red red
        li.bold.green green
        li.bold.gray gray

